setWindowTitle & resize: Sets the application title and defines the initial window dimensions.

QStackedWidget: Creates a container that holds multiple screens (pages) but shows only one at a time.

setCentralWidget: Places the stacked widget as the main content area of the window.

vytvor_menu(): Calls the internal method to build the initial selection screen.

QVBoxLayout: Arranges the title and buttons in a vertical column.

QLabel styling: Creates a centered header with custom CSS for size and spacing.

for pocet in [2, 4, 6]: Iterates through numbers to generate player-count buttons dynamically.

lambda checked, p=pocet: A critical fix for Python loops; it "captures" the current value of pocet so each button remembers its specific number when clicked.

addWidget(menu_widget): Adds the finished menu layout into the QStackedWidget stack.

spust_hru Method (Navigation Logic)
pocet_h parameter: Receives the number of players passed from the clicked button.

print: Acts as a placeholder for the game initialization logic; in a full app, this would switch the QStackedWidget to the actual game screen.
